The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Japan invitation for Gaurav Ghei

Tokyo: Gaurav Gheis brilliant run on the Asian Tour has earned him a special invitation to the UBS Japan Golf Tour championship. 

The Indian is currently seventh on the UBS Asian Tour Order of Merit. 

The tournament, considered the Players Championship of Japan, is to be held from June 28-July 1 at the Shishido Hills Country Club, 90 minutes north-east of Tokyo. 

The prestigious event offers a prize of about $1.25 million. The winner will also receive entry into the $8 million Bridgestone Invitational. 

Ghei has had a great season with a victory at the Pine Valley Beijing Open in April and two top-ten finishes. He is on track to registering his best season on the Asian Tour with more than $210,000 in earnings so far. (PTI) 




